<inglise> COMMISSION REGULATION (EEC) No 2728/88 of 31 August 1988 on the reduction of the buying-in price for wine as referred to in Article 44 of Regulation (EEC) No 822/87 </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;) nr 2728/88 m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 822/87 artiklis 44 osutatud veini kokkuostuhinna alandamise kohta 31. august 1988 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 822/87 of 16 March 1987 on the common organization of the market in wine (1), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 2253/88 (2), and in particular Articles 44 and 81 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 16. m&auml;rtsi 1987. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 822/87 veinituru &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 2253/88, eriti selle artikleid 44 ja 81, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 44 of Council Regulation (EEC) No 822/87 stipulates for certain distillations a reduction in the buying-in price for wine to be paid to producers who have increased alcoholic strength by adding sucrose or by adding concentrated grape must for which they have either received aid under Article 45 of that Regulation or have applied for aid; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 822/87 artikliga 44 on ette n&auml;htud teatavate destilleerimiste puhul veini kokkuostuhinna alandamine, mida makstakse tootjatele, kes on suurendanud alkoholisisaldust, lisades sahharoosi v&otilde;i kontsentreeritud viinamarjavirret, millele tootja on k&otilde;nealuse m&auml;&auml;ruse artikli 45 kohaselt saanud toetust v&otilde;i seda taotlenud; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is very difficult to link the increase in alcoholic strength obtained by each producer to the wine delivered for distillation; whereas because of this the exact determination of the economic advantage accruing to each producer would require an excessive amount of administrative work liable to delay payment of the aid and affect the whole intervention system; whereas the buying-in price should therefore be reduced on the basis of the average increase in the alcoholic strength in each wine-growing zone; whereas in order to avoid the excessive amount of administrative work that would be required to verify the increase in alcoholic strength for every producer the buying-in price for the wine in question delivered for distillation should be reduced by a fixed amount for each zone or zone division; </inglise>
<eesti> v&auml;ga raske on seostada iga tootja poolt saavutatud suurendatud alkoholisisaldust ja destilleerimiseks tarnitavat veini; igale tootjale laekuva majandusliku kasu t&auml;pne kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramine n&otilde;uaks seet&otilde;ttu &uuml;lem&auml;&auml;rast haldust&ouml;&ouml;d, mis viivitaks toetuse maksmist ja m&otilde;jutaks kogu sekkumiss&uuml;steemi; seep&auml;rast tuleks kokkuostuhinda alandada iga viinamarjakasvatusv&ouml;&ouml;ndi alkoholisisalduse keskmise suurendamise p&otilde;hjal; tootjate poolt saavutatud suurendatud alkoholisisalduse kontrollimisest tuleneva &uuml;lem&auml;&auml;rase haldust&ouml;&ouml; v&auml;ltimiseks tuleks destilleerimiseks tarnitud k&otilde;nealuse veini kokkuostuhinda alandada iga v&ouml;&ouml;ndi v&otilde;i selle osa puhul kindla summa v&otilde;rra; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is only fair that producers should receive the full price if they have not increased the alcoholic strength of any part of their table wine by the addition of either sucrose or of concentrated grape must on which the aid provided for in Article 45 of Regulation (EEC) No 822/87 has been received; </inglise>
<eesti> Kui tootjad ei ole oma lauaveini alkoholisisaldust suurendanud, lisades selleks sahharoosi v&otilde;i kontsentreeritud viinamarjavirret, millele nad on saanud m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 822/87 artiklis 45 etten&auml;htud toetust, on neile t&auml;ishinna maksmine &otilde;iglane; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas producers who have increased the alcoholic strength of less of their production than they deliver for distillation should be able to receive the full price for the difference between the volume enriched and that delivered; </inglise>
<eesti> tootjad, kes on suurendanud alkoholisisaldust v&auml;iksemal kogusel kui see, mille nad destilleerimiseks tarnivad, peaksid saama t&auml;ishinda rikastatud ja tarnitud koguse vahelise koguse eest; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the aid for the product obtained by distillation and the price of the products taken over by the intervention agency under the distillation arrangements referred to in Articles 36 and 39 of Regulation (EEC) No 822/87 must be adjusted in line with the reduction in the buying-in price for the wine; </inglise>
<eesti> destilleerimisel saadud tootele antavat toetust ja sekkumisasutuse poolt m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 822/87 artiklites 36 ja 39 osutatud destilleerimiskorra alusel &uuml;le v&otilde;etud toodete hinda tuleb korrigeerida koosk&otilde;las veini kokkuostuhinna alandamisega; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Wine, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las veinituru korralduskomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The buying-in price for wine delivered for distillation under one of the arrangements indicated in Articles 36 (2), 38, 39, 41 and 42 of Regulation (EEC) No 822/87 shall be reduced by an amount to be set before the beginning of each wine year. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;he m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 822/87 artikli 36 l&otilde;ikes 2 ning artiklites 38, 39, 41 ja 42 osutatud korra alusel destilleerimiseks tarnitud veini kokkuostuhinda alandatakse enne iga veiniaasta algust kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud summa v&otilde;rra. </eesti>
<inglise> This amount shall vary by wine-growing zone in accordance with the maximum increase in alcoholic strength indicated in Article 18 (1) and (2) of Regulation (EEC) No 822/87. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev summa erineb viinamarjakasvatusv&ouml;&ouml;ndites vastavalt m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 822/87 artikli 18 l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 osutatud alkoholisisalduse maksimaalsele suurendamisele. </eesti>
<inglise> The reduction referred to in the first subparagraph shall not apply to: </inglise>
<eesti> Esimeses l&otilde;igus nimetatud kokkuostuhinna alandamist ei kohaldata: </eesti>
<inglise> - wine delivered by producers who are located in regions where alcoholic strength may be increased only by the addition of must and who, for the wine year in question, forego all aid made available under Article 45 of Regulation (EEC) No 822/87. </inglise>
<eesti> - veinile, mis on tarnitud tootjate poolt, kes asuvad piirkondades, kus alkoholisisaldust v&otilde;ib suurendada ainult viinamarjavirde lisamise teel ja kes k&otilde;nealusel veiniaastal loobuvad t&auml;ielikult m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 822/87 artiklis 45 etten&auml;htud toetusest. </eesti>
<inglise> These producers shall present to the distiller a copy, stamped by the competent authority designated by the Member State, of a statement waiving entitlement to the aid provided by Commission Regulation (EEC) No 2640/88 (3), </inglise>
<eesti> Need tootjad esitavad destilleerijale liikmesriigi m&auml;&auml;ratud p&auml;deva asutuse templiga koopia kinnitusest, milles loobutakse &otilde;igusest komisjoni m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 2640/88 etten&auml;htud toetusele, </eesti>
<inglise> - wine taken into a distillery after the dates laid down for the various wine-growing zones in Article 23 (3) of Regulation (EEC) No 822/87 and delivered by producers who provide the competent authorities with satisfactory evidence that during the wine year they have neither increased the alcoholic strength of their table wine by adding sucrose nor lodged an application for the aid referred to in Article 45 of the said Regulation in respect of their production. </inglise>
<eesti> - veinile, mis viiakse piiritustehasesse p&auml;rast m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 822/87 artikli 23 l&otilde;ikes 3 eri viinamarjakasvatusv&ouml;&ouml;ndite jaoks kehtestatud kuup&auml;evi ja mida tarnivad tootjad, kes esitavad p&auml;devale asutusele piisavad t&otilde;endid selle kohta, et nad ei ole veiniaasta jooksul oma lauaveini alkoholisisaldust sahharoosi lisamise teel suurendanud ega esitanud taotlust k&otilde;nealuse m&auml;&auml;ruse artiklis 45 osutatud toetuse saamiseks oma toodangule. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> An amount equal to the reduction referred to in paragraph 1 shall be paid, for the quantity of wine delivered for distillation under one of the arrangements referred to in that paragraph, to producers who make application before 1 September to the competent authority either directly or through a distiller and who, in the course of the wine year, have neither increased the alcoholic strength of their table wine production by adding sucrose nor applied for the aid referred to in Article 45 of Regulation (EEC) No 822/87 in respect of such production. </inglise>
<eesti> Tootjatele, kes esitavad ise v&otilde;i destilleerija kaudu sekkumisasutusele taotluse enne 1. septembrit ja kes ei ole veiniaasta jooksul suurendanud oma lauaveinitoodangu alkoholisisaldust sahharoosi lisamise teel ega taotlenud sellisele toodangule m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 822/87 artiklis 45 osutatud toetust, makstakse l&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud alandamisega v&otilde;rdne summa selle veinikoguse eest, mis tarnitakse destilleerimiseks &uuml;he mainitud l&otilde;ikes osutatud korra alusel. </eesti>
<inglise> Producers who apply before 1 September and who, in the course of the wine year, have increased alcoholic strength by adding sucrose or have applied for the said aid only in respect of less of their table wine production than the quantity delivered for distillation under all of the said arrangements during the wine year shall receive the amount indicated in the first subparagraph in respect of the difference between the quantity of table wine the alcoholic strength of which was increased and the quantity that they delivered or had delivered for distillation. </inglise>
<eesti> Tootjatele, kes esitavad taotluse enne 1. septembrit ja kes on veiniaasta jooksul suurendanud alkoholisisaldust sahharoosi lisamise teel v&otilde;i kes on taotlenud mainitud toetust v&auml;iksemale lauaveinitoodangu kogusele kui see, mis veiniaasta jooksul mainitud korra alusel destilleerimiseks tarniti, makstakse esimeses l&otilde;igus osutatud summa suurendatud alkoholisisaldusega lauaveinikoguse ja destilleerimiseks tarnitud v&otilde;i tarnida lastud koguse vahe eest. </eesti>
<inglise> The competent authorities of the Member States may require from these producers any evidence needed to demonstrate the validity of the application. </inglise>
<eesti> Taotluse kehtivuse t&otilde;estamiseks v&otilde;ivad liikmesriikide p&auml;devad asutused k&otilde;nealustelt tootjatelt n&otilde;uda mis tahes t&otilde;endeid. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The second subparagraph of paragraph 2 shall not apply to any quantity delivered by a producer who purchased it. </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ike 2 teist l&otilde;iku ei kohaldata nende koguste suhtes, mille on tarninud need ostnud tootja. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> Paragraphs 1 and 2 shall not apply to producers in Member States that do not authorize natural alcoholic strength by volume to be increased as provided for in Article 18 (1) of Regulation (EEC) No 822/87. </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ikeid 1 ja 2 ei kohaldata tootjate suhtes nendes liikmesriikides, kus m&auml;&auml;ruse 822/87 artikli 18 l&otilde;ikes 1 ette n&auml;htud naturaalse alkoholisisalduse suurendamine mahuprotsentides ei ole lubatud. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> Where wine is delivered for distillation as referred to in Article 1 and where the reduction has been applied to such wine, </inglise>
<eesti> Kui veini on tarnitud destilleerimiseks vastavalt artiklile 1 ja kui sellise veini suhtes on kohaldatud kokkuostuhinna alandamist, v&auml;hendatakse artiklis 1 osutatud alandamisega v&otilde;rdse summa v&otilde;rra: </eesti>
<inglise> - the aid to be paid to the distiller, </inglise>
<eesti> - destilleerijale makstavat toetust, </eesti>
<inglise> - the price to be paid to the distiller for delivery to the intervention agency under Article 36 (6) or 39 (7) of Regulation (EEC) No 822/87, </inglise>
<eesti> -m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 822/87 artikli 36 l&otilde;ike 6 ja artikli 39 l&otilde;ike 7 alusel destilleerijale sekkumisasutusele tarnimise eest makstavat hinda, </eesti>
<inglise> - the EAGGF contribution to expenditure incurred by the intervention agency in taking over alcohol under Article 36 of Regulation (EEC) No 822/87 shall be reduced by an amount equal to the reduction indicated in Article 1. </inglise>
<eesti> - Euroopa P&otilde;llumajanduse Arendus- ja Tagatisfondi panust sekkumisasutuse poolt m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 822/87 artikli 36 alusel alkoholi &uuml;lev&otilde;tmisel tekkitud kuludes. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall adopt all measures required for the verification of data and of compliance with the providions of Article 1. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;tavad k&otilde;ik vajalikud meetmed andmete ja artikli 1 s&auml;tete j&auml;rgimise kontrollimiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> They shall immediately notify these measures to the Commission. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid teavitavad nendest meetmest viivitamata komisjoni. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on 1 September 1988. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub 1. septembril 1988. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. Done at Brussels, 31 August 1988. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
 